      "message": " A meta consideration as we go further into the rabbit hole:\n\n- setters are easy\n- getters are not (or at least are not always efficient)\n\nexample:\n\nsetColor(Color) - easy: we extract the floats and send them to the native instance\nColor getColor() - icky:\n    - Do we allocate a new Color each time?\n    - Do we store the user\u0027s obj on the java side?\n        - if we do, is Color immutable?\n\nNot impossible to reason about for colors, but moving to complex objects like \"shader\", this gets interesting...",
